cs.CR, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IT 

The paper deals with a cybersecurity issue (Man-in-the-Middle attacks) and proposes a novel solution using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves signal processing techniques, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing). The use of autoencoders for modeling patterns suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves network communication and analysis, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
